d for their contributions. Women's challenges are mainly social,\nincluding lack of peer parity and non-inclusive communication from a toxic\nculture. The literature reports ten strategies, which were mapped to six of the\nseven challenges. Based on these results, we provide guidelines for future\nresearch and practice.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 May 2021 18:52:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 22 Dec 2021 17:46:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 5 Jan 2022 15:40:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-06"}
